Comment:
So I am annotating this game,  for one reason, I haven't annotated but one other and I only got about halfway through the game doing it ...  then finished it out later.  The other reason is as per my comment to my opponent...
"I am going to annotate this one since I only partially annotated another, also, annotating against a superior player may help, or at least be humorous reading..."
The Game begins with the first few moves set ...  I think it is safe to say that it's a messed up opening.
I have never done this myself,  don't intend to..
I mean why in the heck would anyone open up his king side like this??
I just don't see it, call me a moron,
yeah,  i can see black doing that
...no sense in just giving it away...
....ok  at least that made sense,  for someone planning on sacrificing the Queen

So here we are,  with the lovely set-up ..  me as white and down 7 points...  yeah,  against a player what...  500 or more points better rated...I should resign and open the bottle,  it would make for a better evening...  but the morning may be rough...so I play on...
there isn't much to do here at this point
he enters in some conditional moves...
I must be a crappy player if he can guess all my moves,  I wonder how far this will go
I have to get some material back.so now I am only down what...  a queen to a Knight and a Bishop?
so I think this is new...

The temptation is to take e4 and get material back,  but I am thinking the more I can keep his King from being in a happy place the better off I am.  then there is the deal with his knight getting down there and forking me at c2.  I have been killed by that.  where is the rum???
MAN!  another conditional move triggered !  how many games of this has he played???!!!  I better check the mini tournament board....  and run to the liquor store...
